Your idea with the `build.gradle` file will work.

You can either specify
```
subprojects {
  group = &quot;org.gradle.sample&quot;
}
```

or alternatively 
```
allprojects {
  group = &quot;org.gradle.sample&quot;
}
```

Please note that both (_subprojects_ and _allprojects_) are all lower-case!
For your current situation it should not matter which of the both you use. If the main (root) project would also publish code, there would be the difference that _subprojects_ only works for the subprojects but not the root project and _allprojects_ - you guess it - works also for the root project.

